<subSubSection lastPageId="171" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="170.[151,1436,1958,2023]" lastBlockId="171.[151,1436,152,719]" lastPageId="171" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1958,1984]" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The small, black bee 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[546,649,1958,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friesei">
<emphasis box="[546,649,1958,1983]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">P. friesei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by its elongate face, which also occurs in related species like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[293,430,1997,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stoeberia">
<emphasis box="[293,430,1997,2022]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">P. stoeberia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[486,587,1997,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friesei">
<emphasis box="[486,587,1997,2022]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">P. friesei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female differs from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[986,1124,1997,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stoeberia">
<emphasis box="[986,1124,1997,2022]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">P. stoeberia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the basal area of propodeum coarsely wrinkled, whereas this area is extensively reticulate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[1035,1173,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stoeberia">
<emphasis box="[1035,1173,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">P. stoeberia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[1187,1289,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulyi">
<emphasis box="[1187,1289,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">P. paulyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,255,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friesei">
<emphasis box="[151,255,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">P. friesei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the punctation of the paraocular area and the discs of T1–T2, which are more densely punctate than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[243,346,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friesei">
<emphasis box="[243,346,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">P. friesei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further, the scutum of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[637,741,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friesei">
<emphasis box="[637,741,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">P. friesei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extensively reticulate, whereas at most finely reticulate anteriorly in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timmermann &amp; Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2009" box="[302,404,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Patellapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulyi">
<emphasis box="[302,404,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">P. paulyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="172" lastPageNumber="173" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="171.[151,1436,152,719]" box="[198,343,306,332]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,306,332]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="171.[151,1436,152,719]" lastBlockId="172.[151,1436,152,758]" lastPageId="172" lastPageNumber="173" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,289,344,370]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Female</emphasis>
. Bl = 6,0– 
<quantity box="[424,509,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" unit="mm" value="6.1">6,1mm</quantity>
. General habitus (
<figureCitation box="[728,846,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Fig. 123e</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,936,344,370]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Head</emphasis>
. L = 
<quantity box="[1008,1145,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.8">1,8–1,9mm</quantity>
; W = 
<quantity box="[1223,1361,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" unit="mm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1,6–1,8mm</quantity>
. Head slightly longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[478,598,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Fig. 123a</figureCitation>
). Integument black except mandibles and malar area partly reddishbrown. Face shiny and with loose, greyish, erect hairs. Mandibles bidentate. Clypeus and supraclypeal area convex in profile. Clypeus finely and sparsely punctate; surface polished. Clypeoantennal distance 
<quantity box="[1346,1432,461,487]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" unit="mm" value="0.5">0,5mm</quantity>
. Supraclypeal area with a few well separated punctures; surface polished. Paraocular area sparsely punctate; surface shiny; partly sculptured. Antennae brownish-black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[910,1042,538,564]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. L = 
<quantity box="[1135,1272,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" unit="mm" value="1.2" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.1">1,1–1,3mm</quantity>
; W (ITS) = 
<quantity box="[151,289,577,603]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1,3–1,5mm</quantity>
. Integument black. Scutum shiny; surface finely reticulate anteriroly; disc densely punctate (i = 1,0d) (
<figureCitation box="[230,349,616,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Fig. 123b</figureCitation>
). Scutellum as illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[692,808,616,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Fig. 123c</figureCitation>
. Scutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum with greyish, erect hairs. Basal area of propodeum as illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[1116,1234,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Fig. 123c</figureCitation>
; propodeum and marginal region of posterior truncation slightly shiny; finely and completely reticulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1169,1248,693,719]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Wings</emphasis>
. Hyaline. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1370,1429,693,719]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Legs</emphasis>
. Integument brownish-black. Vestiture mostly greyish. Ts moderately strongly serrate with 6–7 oblique projections (
<figureCitation box="[306,427,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 123f</figureCitation>
). Bp as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[687,814,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[751,814,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.23" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="g" value="123.0">123g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[842,972,190,216]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Metasoma</emphasis>
. L = 
<quantity box="[1062,1199,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="3.2" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.1">3,1–3,3mm</quantity>
; W = 2,0– 
<quantity box="[1349,1433,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="2.1">2,1mm</quantity>
. Integument brownish-black; margins of T pallid brownish to pale, broadly translucent. Weak apical hair bands on T3–T4 (usually only present laterally). Prepygidial fimbria mostly brownish. Metasomal terga as illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[305,421,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURE 123" captionStartId="171.[151,254,1939,1963]" captionTargetBox="[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-266@171.[283,1303,777,1922]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 123. Patellapis (Ch.) paulyi, female: a. Head (scale=0,5mm); b. Scutum (scale=0,5mm); c. Scutellum and propodeum (scale=0,5mm); d. Metasomal terga (scale=1mm); e. Body (scale=1mm); f. Inner hind tibial spur (scale=100µm); g. Basitibial plate (scale=100µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345800/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 123d</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
